Part 1: The Toolbox (Imports)

    Python

        from ddgs import DDGS
        from fastapi import FastAPI
        from pydantic import BaseModel
        import uvicorn
        import os
        import requests
        import chromadb
        import re
        from dotenv import load_dotenv
        from datetime import datetime

    What it implies: We are pulling pre-built tools into our workspace so we don't have to write
                     thousands of lines of foundational code from scratch.

    Who connects to whom: DDGS connects Python to DuckDuckGo's live news servers.

    FastAPI and uvicorn connect Python to your computer's internet ports.

    BaseModel connects incoming web data to strict Python rules.

    requests connects Python to Groq's cloud AI servers.

    chromadb connects Python to a local folder on your hard drive to store text.

    re connects Python to a text-filtering engine.

    os and load_dotenv connect Python to your hidden .env password file.

    datetime connects Python to your computer's internal clock.

    Output/Example: Nothing prints to the screen. It just loads these tools into the computer's active memory.

